rm - remove files and directories
Executable: /bin/rm.sh
Alias: rm

DESCRIPTION
  Removes files. Directories
  require recursive mode.

USAGE
  rm <path> [path...]
  rm -r <path> [path...]
  rm -f <path> [path...]

OPTIONS
  -r
    Remove directories
    recursively.
  -f
    Ignore missing paths.

NOTES
  Drive roots and read-only
  paths are never deleted.
